As the parent of a one year old and constantly having to smile and nod and criticisms from my own mother, don't start any conversation with "I used to do it like this", "that's not going to help", "why are you doing that?". Giving your son, or daughter in law, a chance to talk and perhaps asking how they feel about the current feeding/bedtime etc would be far more productive. Offer simple help and support and if its accepted then work out detail.



