I have 2&4 year olds. We almost always sit down to dinner at the same time each night and my four year old will sometimes eat with us, ranging anywhere from a few bites to a full adult sized meal, or refuse to eat. Two year old always eats solidly whatever is served. We don't make a big deal out of it and leave his plate on the table, which he often comes back to later when he's hungry. No one knows your kids better than you do. Grandparents can come in and judge a situation without knowing the years of day-to-day back story that has led to certain behaviours. Sometimes parents can't see the forest for the trees but sometimes they just deal with their odd little people the way that works for them.



